      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHARNI'S SECRET (7) failed to come into contention last start after drifting back at Warragul, but prior to that won by 0.8 lengths at this track (24.05) beating Baywara in a Grade 4/5 on May 22. The form from her last run stacks up well. Key runner on her best form. BREAKN' A SWEAT (5) is a consistent runner who is having his first try here. Scored in one of the quickest times on the card (22.85) latest, winning by a neck at Warragul in Grade 4/5. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Expected to feature again. HE'S A COLLINDA (6) flew the lids from out wide with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow fifth (23.03) over 400m at Warragul. Should be about the mark. WHY NOT SEB (1) cannot be underestimated.",
